        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>Replacing a bike tire is easy if you follow these steps carefully. This guide helps you replace the tire safely.</p>
        <h2>Tools Needed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Tire levers</li>
            <li>Wrench</li>
            <li>New tire and tube</li>
            <li>Pump</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Remove the wheel from the bike.</li>
            <li>Use tire levers to remove the old tire.</li>
            <li>Inspect the rim and clean any debris.</li>
            <li>Install the new tube and tire onto the rim.</li>
            <li>Inflate to the recommended pressure and reattach the wheel.</li>
        </ol>
        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Check tire direction markings.</li>
            <li>Ensure tube is not pinched when mounting the tire.</li>
        </ul>
